        <c02 level="item" id="d1e234">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Silas Weir Mitchell</persname>to 
                  <persname>Hester [Horn]</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">[1907] Jun 27</unitdate>
            <physdesc><genreform>ALS,</genreform><extent>3 p.</extent>w/env</physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Says he is delighted with the news of her
                  upcoming marriage to Mr. Bartol; remarks that if Mr.
                  Bartol is like his mother, she must be congratulated;
                  wishes her marital happiness.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e256">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Silas Weir Mitchell</persname>to Board of
                  Directors of "The Players"</unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1911 Jan 21</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>TLS,</genreform>
              <extent>1 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Recommends 
                  <persname>Henry G. Bartol</persname>, his nephew by
                  marriage, to become a member of "The Players."]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e279">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Silas Weir Mitchell</persname>to [ 
                  <persname>Hester Horn Bartol</persname>]</unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">n. d.</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>1 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Asks, "Is nanny too ill to see me?"]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e302">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Silas Weir Mitchell</persname>to
                  [Jim]</unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">n. d.</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>2 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Gives congratulatory wish that the next 
                  <persname>John [Horn]</persname>may be as worthy of
                  the name as the ones who bore it before him.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
